description:
Otis Taylor (born July 30, 1948, Chicago, Illinois, United States) is an American blues musician. He is a 
multi-instrumentalist whose talents include the guitar, banjo, mandolin, harmonica, and vocals. In 2001,
he was awarded a fellowship to the Sundance Film Composers Laboratory.
As of 2008, has released nine blues albums on several record labels. His music tends to focus on the hard 
realities of life, especially relating to the black community. Some common themes in his music are murder, 
racism, poverty, and the need for redemption. To date, Taylor has twelve Blues Music Awards nominations while
White African was named 'Best Artist Debut'
